## v1.1.0 (2026-06-19)

**Changed by:** Re-planning of issue #179 after a NOGO review (stacks on PR #2603, which created v1.0.0 and was already merged).
**Verification:** unverified

### What changed

- Added 4 new Failed Attempts rows refining the same "verify assumptions before finalizing an enforcement-gate plan" theme:
  - Filesystem `Path.rglob("*.md")` walks INTO submodule trees in a meta-repo → use `git ls-files` (the index) which excludes submodules + gitignored worktrees for free.
  - Referencing a `pixi run pytest` harness that does not exist (this meta-repo has no Python test runner; `just test` runs ctest + bash) → make the gate self-testing via a stdlib `--self-test`.
  - An "acknowledged risk" left in a Learnings note does NOT count as resolved — resolve each risk in the plan body.
  - Tighten proximity regexes: require an admonition token (warning/caution/important) AND a verb, plus a negative test asserting a bare verb does not pass.
- Reframed the old "full-tree scan excludes SKIP_DIRS but not submodules" risk as RESOLVED via `git ls-files` (Detailed Step 3, Quick Reference step 3).
- Added Detailed Steps 6–10 (test-runner confirmation, tightened regex, full-index scan, e2e opt-in marker caveat, resolve-risks-in-body discipline).
- Updated Quick Reference with `git ls-files`, `pixi.toml`/`justfile` runner checks, and `--self-test`.
- Updated Results & Parameters with verified index-scan output, test-runner reality, tightened regex, and a refreshed "Open reviewer tasks (UNVERIFIED)" list (git-metadata-in-CI, git-on-PATH, new e2e-only marker convention).
- Updated description and tags (`git-ls-files`, `self-test`, `resolve-not-list-risks`).
- Added `history` frontmatter field and Overview History row.
- Bumped version 1.0.0 → 1.1.0 (minor: new findings + new failed attempts; existing recommendation extended, not replaced).

### Why

The v1.0.0 plan (PR #2603) flagged several gate-design assumptions as reviewer risks but left them unresolved in the plan body; a NOGO review downgraded it for exactly that. Re-planning issue #179 produced concrete resolutions: scope the scan to the git index instead of an rglob filesystem walk (the rglob descended into ~14 submodules and matched files the meta-repo cannot edit), self-test the gate with stdlib instead of an assumed pytest harness, and tighten the proximity regex. These are refinements of the same skill's theme, so this is an amendment (minor bump), not a new skill. Verification stays `unverified` — the gate script was still not executed in CI.

